div.h2: PDE and PTE Bit-Field Layout x86 32-bit Paging
div.p: All flag bits identical in bits 11:0; bits 31:12 differ in purpose

Bit Abbreviations P=Present R/W=Writable U/S=User(1)/Supervisor(0) PWT=Write-Through PCD=Cache-Disable A=Accessed(CPU sets) D=Dirty(CPU sets, PTE only) G=Global(no TLB flush) PS=Page-Size(PDE: 0=4KB, 1=4MB) AVAIL=OS-defined bits 11:9 Selector Rule: P=0 entry invalid; MMU raises #PF. P=1 bits 31:12 valid frame/PT address.
